Interface Population<D>

All Known Subinterfaces:
NEATPopulation<D>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractNEATPopulation, AbstractPopulation, NEATPopulationImpl, PopulationImpl
public interface Population<D>
extends GeneticsObject, java.util.Collection<Genome<D>>

The Population interface is for collections of Genomes and maintaining group statistics as they evolve. The primary attributes of Populations are age, age of last improvement, and next available genome instance number.

Author:
Luis Guimbarda
